<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="310" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,475,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[863,945,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="310">lunatus</emphasis>
, referring to the shape of the sclerite in the appendix bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
